# header
#: Ethical_Decisions/Planning_Research.md:6
msgid "## Summary"
msgstr "## Resumen"

#: Ethical_Decisions/Planning_Research.md:7
msgid "Society continually debate the use of animals in scientific research. "
msgstr ""
"La sociedad continuamente cuestiona el uso de animales en la investigación "
"científica."

#: Ethical_Decisions/Planning_Research.md:8
msgid ""
"The fundamental questions are whether experiments using animals are morally "
"justifiable and whether the potential benefits outweigh the suffering of "
"those animals?"
msgstr ""
"Las preguntas fundamentales son si los experimentos con animales son "
"moralmente justificables y si los posibles beneficios superan el sufrimiento"
" de esos animales."

#: Ethical_Decisions/Planning_Research.md:9
msgid ""
"These questions have been coupled with increasing concern about the poor "
"reproducibility of findings from animal research, due to the impact this has"
" on translation, scientific progress and the use of resources."
msgstr ""
"Estas preguntas se han ligado a una preocupación creciente por la escasa "
"reproducibilidad de los resultados de la investigación con animales, debido "
"al impacto que esto conlleva en el progreso científico y el uso de recursos."

#: Ethical_Decisions/Planning_Research.md:10
msgid ""
"A question that is not often addressed is how those justified experiments "
"are designed, conducted and analysed."
msgstr ""
"Una cuestión que no suele abordarse es cómo se diseñan, cómo se llevan a "
"cabo y cómo se analizan aquellos experimentos debidamente justificados."

#: Ethical_Decisions/Planning_Research.md:11
msgid ""
"Flawed experimental design, inappropriate statistical analysis and "
"inadequate reporting have been flagged as areas for major concern (Kilkenny "
"et al., 2009 (https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0007824), Begley et al., "
"2015 (https://doi.org/10.1161/CIRCRESAHA.114.303819))."
msgstr ""
"El diseño experimental defectuoso, el análisis estadístico inapropiado y los"
" informes inadecuados se han identifcado como las áreas de mayor "
"preocupación (Kilkenny et al., 2009 "
"(https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0007824), Begley et al., 2015 ( "
"https://doi.org/10.1161/CIRCRESAHA.114.303819))."

#: Ethical_Decisions/Planning_Research.md:12
msgid ""
"It is morally incumbent upon us to ensure that animal experiments are "
"appropriately designed, conducted and analysed otherwise the results are at "
"risk of being unreliable."
msgstr ""
"Nos incumbe moralmente asegurarnos de que los experimentos con animales se "
"diseñen, se realicen y se analicen de manera adecuada; de lo contrario, los "
"resultados corren el riesgo de no ser fiables."

#: Ethical_Decisions/Planning_Research.md:13
msgid ""
"If the results are unreliable then the animals used have in effect have been"
" wasted (Ioannidis et al., 2014 "
"(https://doi.org/10.1016/S0140-6736(13)62227-8), de Vries et al., 2014 "
"(https://doi.org/10.1093/ilar/ilu043)).  "
msgstr ""
"Si los resultados no son fiables, entonces los animales utilizados se han "
"utilizado inutilmente (Ioannidis et al., 2014 "
"(https://doi.org/10.1016/S0140-6736(13)62227-8), de Vries et al., 2014 "
"(https://doi.org/10.1093/ilar/ilu043))."

# header
#: Ethical_Decisions/Planning_Research.md:15
msgid "## How this will help you/ why this is useful"
msgstr "## Cómo te ayudará esto/ por qué esto es útil"

#: Ethical_Decisions/Planning_Research.md:16
msgid ""
"Many preclinical researchers do not think of themselves as data scientists."
msgstr ""
"Muchos investigadores preclínicos no se consideran científicos de datos."

#: Ethical_Decisions/Planning_Research.md:17
msgid "This may be primarily because they work with small datasets."
msgstr ""
"Esto puede deberse principalmente a que trabajan con conjuntos de datos "
"pequeños."

#: Ethical_Decisions/Planning_Research.md:18
msgid ""
"However, there are many common open research themes and this chapter aims to"
" assist preclinical scientists in understanding the why, where, when, and "
"how they can employ open research initiatives, some designed specifically "
"for the use by preclinical scientists."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, hay muchos temas de investigación abierta comunes y este "
"capítulo tiene como objetivo ayudar a los científicos preclínicos a "
"comprender por qué, dónde, cuándo y cómo pueden utilizar estas iniciativas "
"de investigación abierta, algunas de las cuales están diseñadas "
"específicamente para científicos preclínicos."

